title: Oceanic Reef Names

embed.description: What is the Nautilus-themed Artificial Reef? The Nautilus artificial reef was the final reward in Ocean Week 2015. Players from all around Oceania played games with specific Ocean Week champions (like Fizz, Nami or Nautilus) to contribute one point per win. The points required to construct the artificial reef was a hefty 275,000 from all Oceanic players.

body: So, I can't find my name. Any one know why? I know I got 10 points and my name isn't offensive, so why can't I find my name?

replies.body:
Hey there,

10 points? Sounds like you're talking about the most recent ocean week, the points earned during the 2016 ocean week will be going towards the Ocean Week community wall (More details coming in the near future).

The Nautilus Reef was for ocean week 2015, which is not the most recent. You only had to earn 3 points during the 2015 ocean week for your name to be on the reef.

You can find more information in [this thread](http://boards.oce.leagueoflegends.com/en/c/miscellaneous/LuyUu4E2-notice-nautilus-reef-and-you).
